This famous thousand-year temple is also the one in the poem "Beyond the Gusu District, from the Hanshan Temple". Tourists often strike the bell in the temple and pray for blessings.

Walk around the well-preserved ancient blocks, watch the bridges and flowing water, visit the literary and artistic shops, and eat delicious food.
Climb or take a boat to visit the only water and land city gate in China — Pan Gate. Walk across the Wumen Bridge and visit the Ruiguang Tower.
It is a good place to climb the mountain. At the top, we can overlook the scenery of Suzhou City, worship Buddha, and pray for blessings in Lingyan Mountain Temple.
